# FlutterSDK Conventions

## Wind UI

- All widgets use `W` prefix: `WDiv`, `WText`, `WButton`, `WInput`, `WSelect`, `WIcon`, `WImage`
- `className` is the primary styling API — utility-first, similar to Tailwind CSS
- Dark mode via `dark:` prefix classes: `className: 'bg-white dark:bg-gray-900'`
- Design tokens for colors, spacing, typography — never hardcode values
- Form widgets: `WFormInput`, `WFormSelect`, `WFormCheckbox`, `WFormDatePicker`

## Magic Framework

- Initialize with `await Magic.init()` in `main()`
- Use Facades for services: `Auth`, `Http`, `Config`, `Cache`, `DB`, `Gate`, `Log`, `Event`
- Controllers extend `MagicController`, views extend `MagicView` or `MagicStatefulView`
- Models extend `Model` with `InteractsWithPersistence` for Eloquent ORM
- Routes use `MagicRoute` with `RouteServiceProvider`
- Forms use `MagicFormData` with `ValidatesRequests` mixin

## General Dart/Flutter

- Explicit types on ALL parameters, return types, and properties
- `@immutable` classes with `const` constructors, `final` fields, and `copyWith`
- DartDoc (`///`) on all public APIs
- 4-space indentation, 120-character max line width
- Multi-line collections with trailing commas — always
- Flutter-native state only: `InheritedWidget` + `ChangeNotifier` — no BLoC/Riverpod/Provider
- English-only code, comments, and documentation
